  "text": "Cyclooxygenase activity. At least 20 mg of muscle was homogenized (2 ml tissue grinder, 440410, Radnoti Glass Technology, Monrovia, CA) in 20 volumes of buffer [100 mM Tris·HCl with proteinase inhibitors (Roche Diagnostics, Chicago, IL)]. After homogenization, samples were centrifuged at 10,000 g for 15 min at 4°C, and the supernatant was retained for assessing COX activity and protein content. COX activity was then assessed using a cyclooxygenase fluorescent activity assay kit (700200; Cayman Chemicals, Ann Arbor, MI). COX-1 and COX-2 activity was assessed by treating separate sample aliquots with selective COX-1 (SC-560, final well concentration: 0.37 M), and COX-2 (DuP-697, final well concentration: 0.33 M) inhibitors were provided with the assay kit. To normalize comparisons within subjects, equal amounts of muscle tissue were assayed at each time point studied. To normalize COX activity to total protein content, an aliquot of the supernatant was assayed, as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
